y’, a byname of the goddesses Lakshmi and Saraswati. Also widely used as an honorific title."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":22,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705197,"age":95,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"John Sr Cooke was born in 1360 as the son of John Cooke. He had at least 1 daughter with Machyn Deneschines. He died in England."},"et":{"1360–":"1360–Surnud","1360–Male":"1360–Surnud","1361–Female":"1361–Surnud","1396–1424":"1396–1424","1330–Male":"1330–Surnud","1424":"1424","1455":"1455","1396":"1396","1330":"1330","1361":"1361","1360":"1360","1382":"1382","Lavenham, Suffolk, England":"Lavenham, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England"},"fi":{"1360–":"1360–Kuollut","1360–Male":"1360–Kuollut","1361–Female":"1361–Kuollut","1396–1424":"1396–1424","1330–Male":"1330–Kuollut","1424":"1424","1455":"1455","1396":"1396","1330":"1330","1361":"1361","1360":"1360","1382":"1382","Lavenham, Suffolk, England":"Lavenham, Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"England"},"fr":{"1360–":"1360–Décédé","1360–Male":"1360–Décédé","1361–Female":"136